HEADWORD: Tetrolic
<hw>Tet*rol"ic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, an acid,
<chform>C3H3.CO2H</chform>, of the acetylene series, homologous with
propiolic acid, obtained as a white crystalline substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

